WEBVTT

00:01.250 --> 00:02.670
[MAL] YOU HAVE FUN, HOT STUFF?

00:02.710 --> 00:04.710
[ROSE] OH, ARE YOU KIDDING?

00:04.750 --> 00:07.210
TASTING MENU AT RAYMOND'S?

00:07.250 --> 00:09.300
THE BEST HUSBAND IN THE WORLD.

00:09.340 --> 00:11.090
SOMEBODY RAISED YOU
RIGHT, MALACHY DOYLE.

00:11.130 --> 00:13.640
SO, WHAT'LL WE HAVE
FOR DESSERT.

00:14.300 --> 00:15.300
&lt;MOANING&gt;

00:15.350 --> 00:16.390
IS THAT YOU?

00:16.430 --> 00:18.100
NO. JUST A SEC.

00:18.140 --> 00:19.430
&lt;MOANING&gt;

00:19.470 --> 00:20.520
&lt;SCREAM&gt;

00:20.560 --> 00:21.600
&lt;THUD&gt;

00:21.640 --> 00:23.190
WHAT IN GOD'S NAME.
WHAT, WHAT IS--

00:23.230 --> 00:24.480
CHRIST, DADDY. HEY!

00:24.520 --> 00:26.270
KATHLEEN, WHO IS--
WHAT ARE YOU--

00:26.310 --> 00:27.650
-UH...
-WHEN DID YOU GET HERE?

00:27.690 --> 00:29.400
TONIGHT. COOL, HEY?

00:30.190 --> 00:31.150
HEY.

00:31.190 --> 00:32.900
HEY, DADDY,
YOU'VE MET ERIC BEFORE.

00:32.950 --> 00:34.240
HE'S GONNA BE STAYING WITH US.

00:34.280 --> 00:35.160
HEY. OH! SORRY.

00:35.200 --> 00:36.490
-HI.
-HEY, ROSE.

00:36.530 --> 00:37.620
HI, SWEETHEART.

00:37.660 --> 00:38.700
YOU HAPPY TO SEE ME?

00:38.740 --> 00:40.370
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH,
YEAH, OF COURSE.

00:40.410 --> 00:42.120
PUT A SHIRT ON. NOW.

00:42.160 --> 00:44.500
&lt;CHEERING&gt;

00:48.340 --> 00:49.800
[JAKE] YEAH, OF COURSE
I WANT TO SEE HER,

00:49.840 --> 00:52.090
BUT HONESTLY, I HAVE PLANS.

00:52.130 --> 00:54.760
BUT IF YOU WANT, I'LL COME
OVER TO THE HOUSE NOW.

00:54.800 --> 00:55.890
&lt;BANGING&gt;

00:55.930 --> 00:56.970
&lt;MUMBLING&gt;

00:57.010 --> 00:58.930
HELLO?

00:58.970 --> 01:00.970
DAD, I'LL CALL YOU BACK.

01:04.350 --> 01:07.230
WHOEVER YOU ARE, I, UH...

01:09.150 --> 01:11.610
OKAY, THIS IS PROBABLY ABOUT
THE MONEY I OWE YOU.

01:11.650 --> 01:15.070
I UNDERSTAND THAT.
AND I, UM, I JUST, UH...

01:18.830 --> 01:20.540
GARRISON STEELE?

01:20.580 --> 01:21.580
WHAT THE--

01:22.080 --> 01:23.620
OW!

01:24.040 --> 01:25.120
AWWWW.

01:27.210 --> 01:30.250
JAKE DOYLE.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
IN MY HOUSE?

01:30.300 --> 01:33.460
STUPID.
YOU'RE IN MY APARTMENT.

01:33.510 --> 01:37.680
OF COURSE I AM.
IT IS DISGUSTING.

01:37.720 --> 01:39.510
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

01:39.550 --> 01:41.850
WOULD YOU LIKE A DRINK?

01:44.100 --> 01:46.270
&lt;VOMITING&gt;

01:49.520 --> 01:50.650
OH, DEAR GOD.

01:50.690 --> 01:52.730
&lt;THEME MUSIC PLAYING&gt;

01:56.110 --> 01:57.200
♪ OH, YEAH

01:57.240 --> 01:58.740
♪ OH, YEAH

01:58.780 --> 01:59.990
♪ OH, YEAH

02:00.030 --> 02:02.240
♪ OH, YEAH

02:02.290 --> 02:05.290
♪ OH, YEAH

02:05.330 --> 02:08.250
♪ OH, YEAH

02:08.290 --> 02:10.960
♪ OH, YEAH! ♪

02:11.000 --> 02:12.550
YOU'VE GOTTA GET
STEELE OUT OF HERE.

02:12.590 --> 02:15.510
I'D LOVE TO JAKE, BUT
KATHLEEN'S GOT SOME FRIEND OF
HER'S - SOME GUY,

02:15.550 --> 02:18.180
ERIC, OR SOMETHING -
AND IF I BRING
ANOTHER PERSON INTO THE HOUSE,

02:18.220 --> 02:19.340
I'M AFRAID ROSE IS GONNA
LEAVE ME.

02:19.390 --> 02:22.100
I DON'T CARE!
GARRISON STEELE THREW UP
ON MY FLOOR.

02:22.140 --> 02:24.560
MAYBE IT'S LIKE A
GIFT OR SOMETHING.
HE MUST HAVE MISSED YOU.

02:24.600 --> 02:26.180
THAT'S SO HILARIOUS.

02:26.230 --> 02:30.400
SHE'S ONLY JUST LANDED
AND, UH, THERE'S THIS SCENE
WITH THIS GUY.

02:30.440 --> 02:36.360
I DON'T CARE ABOUT ANY
GUY, OKAY? JUST DON'T LEAVE ME
ALONE WITH GARRISON STEELE.

02:36.400 --> 02:40.320
IT'S SO GALLANT
OF YOU TO LET ME STAY HERE
IN THE JAKE-CAVE.

02:40.370 --> 02:43.830
I APPRECIATE IT
MORE THAN WORDS CAN EXPRESS.

02:43.870 --> 02:47.250
MALACHY! MY OLD FRIEND.

02:49.620 --> 02:52.340
YEAH, IT'S NICE TO
SEE YOU, GARRISON. YOU OKAY?

02:52.380 --> 02:55.260
WHY, YES, ACTUALLY, I AM.

02:55.300 --> 02:58.590
YOU KNOW,
IF YOU'D CALLED,
I COULD HAVE BOOKED A HOTEL.

02:58.630 --> 03:00.220
THERE'S NO NEED.
I-- I LIKE IT HERE.

03:00.260 --> 03:01.510
I MEANT FOR ME.

03:01.550 --> 03:02.890
I BROUGHT A GIFT.

03:02.930 --> 03:06.270
IT'S ALL THE WAY FROM THE
SOUTH OF FRANCE. RIGHT HERE.

03:08.430 --> 03:11.060
SO-- SO WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

03:11.100 --> 03:14.360
YOU NEED ME TO SIGN OVER
THE MOVIE RIGHTS FOR THE SPECIAL DETECTIVE  OR...

03:14.400 --> 03:17.030
&lt;CRYING&gt;

03:20.570 --> 03:22.370
I'M SORRY.

03:24.660 --> 03:26.790
I SHOULDN'T HAVE COME.

03:26.830 --> 03:28.000
BUT I NEED YOUR HELP.

03:28.040 --> 03:30.830
I DO-- I TRULY DO.

03:30.870 --> 03:32.960
WHAT'S WRONG.
YOU GET A BAD REVIEW?

03:33.000 --> 03:36.170
IGNORE HIM, GARRISON.
JUST TELL US WHAT HAPPENED.

03:36.210 --> 03:42.260
IT'S THE LOVE OF MY LIFE.
TAMARA. SHE'S GONE MISSING.

03:42.890 --> 03:44.390
YOU LOVE, LIKE, A HUMAN?

03:44.430 --> 03:45.470
JAKE.

03:45.510 --> 03:50.480
FRIEND TO FRIEND.
MAN TO MAN. I NEED YOUR HELP.

03:50.520 --> 03:52.270
GIVE US A MINUTE, GARRISON.

03:53.770 --> 03:57.280
HE'S IN ROUGH SHAPE HERE.
BE A MAN. LET'S HELP HIM.

03:57.320 --> 03:58.780
WHY DON'T YOU HELP HIM
YOURSELF?

03:58.820 --> 03:59.860
&lt;THUD&gt;

04:01.990 --> 04:03.820
I THINK THIS MIGHT BE A
TWO-MAN JOB.

04:10.040 --> 04:12.540
SO, TINNY. YOU'RE SICK.
I CALLED SCHOOL.

04:12.580 --> 04:13.790
YOU'VE GOT A FEVER.

04:13.830 --> 04:15.040
REALLY? THAT CAME ON FAST.

04:15.080 --> 04:16.380
IT'S NOT CONTAGIOUS, IS IT?

04:16.420 --> 04:17.670
MOM, I WANNA HANG, I DO,

04:17.710 --> 04:19.760
BUT I GOT THIS BIG TEST
COMING UP...

04:19.800 --> 04:21.340
UH, I'M GONNA GO WAIT IN
THE CAR.

04:21.380 --> 04:23.180
BABY, YOU KNOW WHAT?

04:23.220 --> 04:28.220
WE NEED SOME CATCH-UP TIME,
AND WHO IS GOING TO HELP ME
PUT ALL MY STUFF AWAY?

04:28.260 --> 04:30.270
OKAY, FINE.

04:30.310 --> 04:32.940
I'M GONNA GO GRAB A SHOWER.

04:35.350 --> 04:36.400
SO WHAT'S WITH BUDDY?

04:36.440 --> 04:38.480
AND WHY DOESN'T HE WEAR ANY
CLOTHES?

04:38.520 --> 04:42.860
HE'S JUST A FRIEND, BABY.
IT'S COOL.
HE'S GONNA HANG WITH US TODAY.

04:46.240 --> 04:49.240
YOU KNOW, I ACTUALLY
SHOULD GO TO SCHOOL.

04:49.290 --> 04:53.290
THIS TEST IS HUGE, AND I HAVE
SO MUCH TO CATCH UP ON.

04:53.330 --> 04:55.460
HAVE FUN WITH
NAKED NEWS THOUGH.

05:00.420 --> 05:04.340
SO, UP AHEAD IS WHERE
MY LOVELY TARA LIVES.

05:04.380 --> 05:05.340
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

05:05.380 --> 05:08.100
TARA? I THOUGHT YOU SAID HER
NAME WAS TAMARA.

05:08.140 --> 05:10.100
TAMARA, OF COURSE.
IT MUST BE THE STRESS.

05:10.140 --> 05:11.890
WHAT COLOR ARE TAMARA'S EYES?

05:11.930 --> 05:13.480
I-- I BELIEVE THEY HAVE
A JADE HUE.

05:13.520 --> 05:14.480
HMM...

05:14.520 --> 05:17.230
AND WHERE DID YOU TWO MEET?

05:17.270 --> 05:19.650
THE LAST TIME I WAS
HERE IN TOWN.

05:19.690 --> 05:21.400
RIGHT.
WHAT'S HER BEST FRIEND'S NAME?

05:21.440 --> 05:22.400
HER FAVORITE COLOR?
HER FAVORITE FOOD?

05:22.440 --> 05:24.450
-HER FAVORITE PERFUME?
-GARRISON?

05:24.490 --> 05:28.320
WELL... WE DIDN'T TALK A LOT
IF YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

05:28.370 --> 05:30.370
YOU KNOW, I AM SMART
ENOUGH TO KNOW WHEN I'M BEING

05:30.410 --> 05:33.790
PLAYED BY A...
ALCOHOLIC HACK BUFFOON.

05:33.830 --> 05:38.170
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.
YOU ARE SUCH A GOOD DETECTIVE.

05:38.210 --> 05:39.380
IT'S ALL ABOUT A BOOK.

05:39.420 --> 05:42.050
-REALLY?
-THAT'S WHY WE'RE HERE?
A BOOK?

05:42.090 --> 05:45.010
I NEED A BOOK, AND
THE SPECIAL DETECTIVE  SERIES

05:45.050 --> 05:46.180
IS A GUARANTEED HIT.

05:46.220 --> 05:47.430
AND, WELL I WANTED...

05:47.470 --> 05:50.010
I'M IN A BIT OF A
PICKLE AND I NEED YOUR HELP.

05:50.050 --> 05:52.470
WAIT, WAIT, PLEASE!
I'M ON BENDED KNEE.

05:52.520 --> 05:53.980
I IMPLORE YOU.

05:54.020 --> 05:57.600
OKAY, FIRST OF ALL, WHEN
SOMEONE SAYS THEY'RE ON
"BENDED KNEE",

05:57.650 --> 05:59.060
THEY USUALLY,
ACTUALLY KNEEL DOWN.

05:59.110 --> 06:01.230
WELL, UH, MY KNEES
AREN'T SO GOOD.

06:01.270 --> 06:03.150
TAMARA BOWLER. SHE'S
ACCUSED OF STEALING FROM THE

06:03.190 --> 06:05.780
DANISH CONSULATE, WHERE SHE
WORKS AS AN ASSISTANT.

06:05.820 --> 06:08.570
SHE'S UNDER HOUSE ARREST
UNTIL THEY TRY HER IN DENMARK.

06:08.610 --> 06:11.450
THIS SOUNDS LIKE A TERRIBLE
IDEA FOR A NOVEL,
EVEN FOR YOU!

06:11.490 --> 06:15.000
I'LL JUST CALL IT
SOMETHING LIKE, THE AMBASSADOR TO MURDER,

06:15.040 --> 06:17.330
AND IT'LL SELL LIKE HOTCAKES.

06:17.670 --> 06:19.920
&lt;SIGH&gt;

06:19.960 --> 06:21.460
HOW MUCH ARE WE GETTING PAID?

06:21.500 --> 06:24.670
I'LL GIVE YOU A CUT
OF THE PROFITS.

06:29.140 --> 06:32.140
MALACHY.

06:32.180 --> 06:34.810
PLEASE DO NOT BE
INTIMIDATED BY MY
PRESENCE HERE.

06:34.850 --> 06:38.730
JUST PRETEND YOU'RE A
CHARACTER IN ONE OF MY NOVELS.

06:38.770 --> 06:40.150
WHO ARE YOU?

06:40.190 --> 06:42.860
I'M STARTING TO LIKE THIS
GIRL ALREADY.

06:42.900 --> 06:45.150
NOT A FAN OF THE
MYSTERY OEUVRE?

06:45.190 --> 06:47.610
NO. ACTUALLY, MYSTERIES
ARE MY FAVORITE.
HE'S A WRITER.

06:47.650 --> 06:50.240
I-- I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
YOU SAID YOU WERE
INVESTIGATORS,

06:50.280 --> 06:52.870
THAT YOU COULD HELP ME WITH MY
LEGAL PROBLEMS.

06:52.910 --> 06:56.540
YEAH, IT'S WHAT YOU'D
CALL COMPLICATED.

06:56.580 --> 07:00.000
UH, WHY DON'T YOU JUST
START BY TELLING US WHAT
HAPPENED.

07:00.040 --> 07:03.960
I DON'T HAVE MUCH TO SAY.
I'M INNOCENT AND THEY'RE
USING ME AS A SCAPEGOAT.

07:04.000 --> 07:05.090
WHO IS?

07:05.130 --> 07:06.960
THE EMBASSY. IT'S LUDICROUS.

07:07.010 --> 07:08.970
WHAT ARE YOU ACCUSED OF
STEALING EXACTLY?

07:09.010 --> 07:11.550
NO IDEA. HONESTLY.

07:11.590 --> 07:14.180
EITHER WAY,
THE POLICE THINK I DO,
AND NOW I'M SADDLED WITH THIS.

07:15.220 --> 07:16.270
FLAWLESS SKIN?

07:17.100 --> 07:18.520
I'M SORRY?

07:18.560 --> 07:21.600
IGNORE HIM. IT'S KIND OF
HIS COURTING RITUAL.

07:21.650 --> 07:23.480
WE'RE DONE HERE. GOODBYE.

07:23.520 --> 07:25.610
STEELE! WE JUST STARTED
TALKING TO HER.

07:25.650 --> 07:29.490
GENIUS. IT'S IN THE
MIND, NOT IN THE MOUTH, AND

07:29.530 --> 07:31.530
SOLUTION COMES FROM WITHIN,

07:31.570 --> 07:35.660
NOT FROM...
MAY I PLEASE USE YOUR
WASHROOM?

07:35.700 --> 07:38.540
OH, OF COURSE. UH, DOWN
THE HALL AND TO THE LEFT.

07:38.580 --> 07:40.580
THANK YOU.

07:40.620 --> 07:44.040
I HAVE TO SAY, I'M NOT
SURE HOW YOU'RE
SUPPOSED TO BE HELPING ME.

07:44.090 --> 07:46.250
IS THIS NORMALLY HOW
YOUR INVESTIGATIONS WORK?

07:46.300 --> 07:48.010
-NO.
-&lt;DOOR BELL&gt;

07:48.050 --> 07:50.170
WHO IS THAT NOW? EXCUSE ME.

07:53.390 --> 07:55.680
HE'S A MESS.
SOMETHING'S NOT RIGHT HERE.

07:55.720 --> 07:56.600
YEAH, IT'S CALLED WHISKEY.

07:56.640 --> 07:58.470
LOOK, GO CHECK ON HIM
BEFORE HE PASSES OUT.

07:58.520 --> 07:59.930
I'LL DISTRACT TAMARA.

07:59.980 --> 08:01.560
DISTRACT HER FROM WHAT?

08:01.600 --> 08:03.650
MY WORK HERE IS DONE.

08:03.690 --> 08:07.730
STEELE, WHY DO YOU HAVE A
PAIR OF UNDERWEAR STICKING OUT
OF YOUR POCKET?

08:07.780 --> 08:09.530
PANTIES? IMPOSSIBLE.

08:09.570 --> 08:10.820
-I HATE THAT WORD.
- PANTIES!

08:10.860 --> 08:12.450
SHH!

08:12.490 --> 08:14.160
OH, IT MUST BE RESEARCH.

08:14.200 --> 08:16.910
IT HELPS DEVELOP THE
CHARACTER WHEN YOU KNOW WHAT

08:16.950 --> 08:19.830
THEY WEAR AT THE MOST INTIMATE
MOMENTS.

08:19.870 --> 08:23.620
TO BE HONEST, I'M
ACTUALLY STARTING TO
WORRY ABOUT YOU HERE.

08:23.670 --> 08:25.590
[TAMARA] LET GO OF ME!
YOU'RE HURTING ME.

08:25.630 --> 08:27.040
[MAL]
HEY, TAKE IT EASY, BUDDY.

08:27.090 --> 08:29.840
[GERHARDT] COME ON,
YOU WERE THE ONLY ONE
WHO HAD THE--

08:29.880 --> 08:34.800
LOOK, I DON'T KNOW WHO YOU ARE
OR WHAT YOU HAVE TO
DO WITH THIS, SO BACK OFF!

08:34.840 --> 08:37.890
&lt;SCREAM&gt;
&lt;CRASH&gt;

08:37.930 --> 08:40.060
I WILL FIND WHAT YOU TOOK.
ALL RIGHT?

08:40.640 --> 08:42.520
&lt;CLICK&gt;

08:42.560 --> 08:45.690
I'M SORRY ABOUT THE VASE.
IT WAS, YOU KNOW, THE ONLY
THING I COULD FIND.

08:45.730 --> 08:47.900
BYE.

08:47.940 --> 08:49.610
YOU ALL RIGHT, SKIPPER?

08:49.650 --> 08:52.570
LOOK, I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU PEOPLE WANT FROM ME, BUT
I THINK IT'S TIME YOU LEFT.

08:52.610 --> 08:55.620
HE DROPPED THIS.
IT'S A COCKTAIL RECEPTION

08:55.660 --> 08:57.990
AT GOVERNMENT HOUSE
FOR THE DANISH CONSULATE.

08:58.030 --> 09:00.120
I'M VERY BIG IN DENMARK.

09:00.160 --> 09:02.200
ARE THOSE MY PANTIES?

09:02.250 --> 09:06.580
LEOPARD PRINT SAYS A
LOT ABOUT A WOMAN.

09:07.250 --> 09:10.420
GET OUT! OUT!

09:14.510 --> 09:16.340
SO, THIS INVITE ONLY
ADMITS ONE.

09:16.390 --> 09:17.850
SO IF YOU WANT TO FIND OUT
MORE ABOUT THE GUY WHO

09:17.890 --> 09:21.430
SMASHED A VASE OVER
MALACHY'S HEAD, I WAS THINKING
YOU'LL NEED MORE INVITES.

09:21.470 --> 09:23.020
-GOOD JOB.
-OH, THANKS.

09:23.060 --> 09:25.770
THANKS. MOST OF IT WAS
PHOTOSHOP, BUT THE
HOLOGRAM WAS REALLY HARD.

09:25.810 --> 09:27.730
I ACTUALLY USED
OLD HOCKEY CARDS,

09:27.770 --> 09:30.980
BUT I FOUND A
TERRY RYAN ROOKIE IN THERE,
WHICH I REALLY, REALLY NEEDED.

09:31.030 --> 09:33.070
THAT'S PRETTY SMART, HUH?

09:33.780 --> 09:35.820
YEAH.

09:35.860 --> 09:39.200
"YOUNG AND INDUSTRIOUS DES
BEAMS WITH APPROVAL FROM HIS

09:39.240 --> 09:41.160
"GREAT FRIEND AND MENTOR,

09:41.200 --> 09:43.750
"JAKE DOYLE."

09:43.790 --> 09:46.960
SO, I WAS THINKING, IF YOU
NEED A PLUS-ONE,
I'M MORE THAN AVAILABLE.

09:47.000 --> 09:48.710
-SURE, WE'LL KEEP YOU IN MIND.
-EXCELLENT.

09:48.750 --> 09:51.800
-ROSE, WHAT HAVE YOU GOT?
-TAMARA HERE IS ACCUSED OF

09:51.840 --> 09:54.340
STEALING AN UNKNOWN ITEM
OUT OF A DIPLOMATIC POUCH.

09:54.380 --> 09:55.630
&lt;LAUGHING&gt;

09:55.670 --> 09:57.470
IT'S PRONOUNCED "POOCH".

09:57.510 --> 09:59.260
SO THIS WHOLE THING WAS
ABOUT A DOG.

09:59.300 --> 10:02.970
NO DES, IT'S A PACKAGE
THAT DIPLOMATS CAN SEND INTO
THE COUNTRY WITHOUT

10:03.020 --> 10:04.770
HAVING IT SEARCHED
OR CHECKED THROUGH
CUSTOMS.

10:04.810 --> 10:06.440
&lt;YAWN&gt;

10:06.480 --> 10:08.310
ARE WE KEEPING YOU UP
THERE, COCKY, OR WHAT?

10:08.350 --> 10:11.610
TV DID. VOLUME ON BUST
APPARENTLY. SORRY.

10:11.650 --> 10:14.440
YEAH, KATHLEEN LIKES IT LOUD.

10:14.490 --> 10:15.740
SHE LIKES THE TV LOUD.

10:15.780 --> 10:17.820
TAMARA COULD HAVE TAKEN
ANYTHING FROM THAT POUCH.

10:17.860 --> 10:20.830
GUNS, MONEY, DRUGS, ANYTHING.

10:20.870 --> 10:23.240
SO WHAT ABOUT THIS GUY?
ANYTHING ON HIM?

10:23.290 --> 10:24.620
NO, NOTHING YET.

10:24.660 --> 10:28.420
STEELE... GIVE ME THIS.

10:28.460 --> 10:32.460
THE MYSTERY MAN. DO YOU KNOW
HIM? YOU DUCKED THE MINUTE
YOU LAID EYES ON HIM.

10:32.500 --> 10:35.300
I WAS SIMPLY MOVING TO A
MORE ADVANTAGEOUS PLACE TO

10:35.340 --> 10:38.510
RECORD HIS MOVEMENTS
FOR MY ART.

10:38.550 --> 10:39.840
UNDER THE CHESTERFIELD.

10:39.890 --> 10:42.560
NO, I'VE NEVER SEEN
HIM BEFORE IN MY LIFE.

10:42.600 --> 10:44.970
WE'RE GOING TO HAVE TO GO TO
THIS DANISH COCKTAIL THING

10:45.020 --> 10:46.930
IF WE'RE GONNA ASK THE
MYSTERY MAN ANY QUESTIONS.

10:46.980 --> 10:49.020
HOPE YOU PACKED YOUR TUX,
GARRISON.

10:49.060 --> 10:50.690
OF COURSE I DID.
DO YOU THINK I'M AN ANIMAL?

10:50.730 --> 10:52.650
&lt;PHONE RINGING&gt;

10:54.820 --> 10:56.240
[ALL] NIKKI?

10:56.280 --> 10:59.910
I THINK WE SHOULD STAKE
OUT TAMARA HERE,
SEE WHO'S COMING AND GOING.

10:59.950 --> 11:02.620
UH, JAKE YOU'RE WITH GARRISON.
ROSE, YOU'RE WITH ME.

11:02.660 --> 11:03.740
YEAH, LET'S DO IT.

11:03.780 --> 11:06.910
EXCELLENT PLAN,
DESERVES A TOAST.

11:13.840 --> 11:15.460
&lt;PARTY CHATTER&gt;

11:24.560 --> 11:25.810
LESLIE.

11:25.850 --> 11:28.390
-JAKE. HI.
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

11:28.430 --> 11:30.690
CAN'T A GIRL GO OUT
WITHOUT HAVING TO GET YOUR
PERMISSION?

11:30.730 --> 11:32.860
RELAX, B'Y.
IT WAS A SIMPLE QUESTION.

11:32.900 --> 11:35.320
YEAH, AND I GAVE YOU A
SIMPLE ANSWER.
MIND YOUR OWN BUSINESS.

11:35.860 --> 11:37.610
&lt;SCOFFS&gt;

11:37.650 --> 11:42.200
SO ARE YOU ALONE,
ARE YOU HERE WITH SOMEONE,
ARE YOU LOOKING FOR SOMEONE?

11:42.240 --> 11:44.780
I'VE GOT MY GUN, JAKE.
DON'T PUSH ME.

11:44.830 --> 11:47.750
WELL... I MEAN, I HAVE NO
IDEA WHERE YOU COULD HAVE THAT
GUN STASHED,

11:47.790 --> 11:50.920
BUT WHEREVER IT IS,
IT'S A VERY LUCKY FIREARM.

11:54.540 --> 12:00.010
OH, I GET IT. YOU'RE HERE WITH
BUDDY. I GUESS YOU'RE INTO
THE TALLER,

12:00.050 --> 12:01.510
BETTER-LOOKING-THAN-ME TYPE.

12:01.550 --> 12:04.090
-GOODBYE, JAKE.
-NO, NO, WAIT. LESLIE,

12:04.140 --> 12:05.760
PLEASE.

12:06.720 --> 12:08.180
YOU LOOK SPECTACULAR.

12:08.220 --> 12:09.600
LOOK, WHATEVER.

12:09.640 --> 12:11.560
COME HERE TO ME.

12:11.600 --> 12:16.730
MY DAD TAUGHT ME HOW
TO TIE ONE OF THESE, IN CASE
MY HUSBAND NEEDED IT.

12:16.770 --> 12:18.730
HIS WORDS.

12:18.780 --> 12:20.570
SO ARE YOU IN THE MARKET?

12:20.610 --> 12:22.990
IN CASE YOU HAVEN'T
NOTICED, OR YOU'RE UNABLE TO

12:23.030 --> 12:28.830
READ THE SIGNS, I'M HERE ON A
DATE WITH ANOTHER MAN,

12:28.870 --> 12:32.500
WHO ISN'T YOU.
IS THAT CLEAR ENOUGH FOR YOU?

12:32.540 --> 12:34.420
SO YOU DON'T WANT TO
MARRY ME, THEN?

12:34.460 --> 12:38.710
NIKKI! NIKKI, HELLO.
LOVELY TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

12:38.750 --> 12:42.630
STEELE, SHUT UP.
THIS IS LESLIE.
YOU TWO HAVE ALREADY MET.

12:43.880 --> 12:47.050
-A FEW TIMES. HI.
-OF COURSE IT'S LESLIE.

12:47.100 --> 12:51.350
I SHOULD HAVE KNOWN FROM
THE LONGING IN HER EYES
FOR YOU.

12:51.390 --> 12:55.060
OH MY, IT'S SO TRANSPARENT.
IT'S ALMOST SHOCKING REALLY.

12:55.100 --> 12:57.190
NOT LIKELY.

12:57.230 --> 13:00.690
WELL, IF YOU NEED ANY
HELP REMOVING THAT DRESS
LATER ON,

13:00.730 --> 13:03.150
I HAVE A FREE HAND. OR TWO.

13:03.200 --> 13:06.780
STEELE! LOOK,
I'M-- I'M SORRY ABOUT HIM.

13:06.820 --> 13:08.490
I'LL SEE YOU AND, UH,

13:08.530 --> 13:11.540
YOUR NEW WING MAN LATER.

13:11.580 --> 13:12.960
ENCHANTE.

13:15.250 --> 13:16.580
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?

13:16.630 --> 13:18.920
PLEASE EXCUSE MY LACK OF TACT.

13:18.960 --> 13:21.420
I'VE HAD A HARROWING
TIME IN DENMARK,

13:21.460 --> 13:24.220
AND I'VE ALWAYS
BEEN RATHER SUSCEPTIBLE
TO JETLAG.

13:24.260 --> 13:28.100
DENMARK? WHAT IS THIS DENMARK?
YOU TOLD ME YOU
TRAVELED FROM FRANCE.

13:28.140 --> 13:29.260
YOU'RE DRUNK!

13:29.310 --> 13:30.720
&lt;PHONE RINGING&gt;

13:32.730 --> 13:35.020
HELLO? OH,
IT HAS BEEN TOO LONG.

13:35.060 --> 13:36.350
ANYWAYS, HE'S RIGHT HERE.

13:36.400 --> 13:40.070
NIKKI. FIRST LESLIE,
AND NOW THE EX-WIFE.

13:40.110 --> 13:45.860
OH, JAKEY BOY, YOUR CLOSET
DOOR IS WIDE OPEN TONIGHT.

13:45.900 --> 13:49.120
-WHY DO YOU EVEN HAVE MY
PHONE?
-HA!

13:49.160 --> 13:51.540
-HI.
-YOU'RE AVOIDING ME, JAKE.

13:51.580 --> 13:53.910
YEAH, I AM, ACTUALLY.

13:53.950 --> 13:57.290
WE NEED TO TALK,
DON'T YOU THINK?
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED?

13:57.330 --> 13:59.880
YEAH, OR WE COULD TRY NOT
TALKING FOR ONCE, YOU KNOW?

13:59.920 --> 14:02.880
-WE COULD JUST DO IT
OVER TEXTS.
-JAKE!

14:02.920 --> 14:06.510
I KNOW. YOU'RE RIGHT.
I'M IN THE MIDDLE OF SOMETHING
RIGHT NOW. CAN WE TALK LATER?

14:06.550 --> 14:08.680
-OKAY, FINE. I'LL CALL YOU.
-ALL RIGHT.

14:12.180 --> 14:13.470
SO I--

14:13.520 --> 14:18.940
I TELL THEM ALL THEY CAN SUCK
IT. AND THEY DIDN'T! HA!

14:18.980 --> 14:21.070
WHERE'S SHE GOING?

14:21.110 --> 14:26.650
HEADS UP, STEELE. THERE'S
OUR MYSTERY MAN FROM TAMARA'S.

14:27.530 --> 14:29.990
- GOOD AFTERNOON!
-&lt;CLINKING&gt;

14:30.030 --> 14:31.910
QUIET. QUIET PLEASE.
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

14:31.950 --> 14:35.540
HELLO. HELLO.
I WANTED TO THANK YOU FOR

14:35.580 --> 14:38.870
THROWING THIS PARTY AS A
LAUNCH FOR MY NEWEST NOVEL IN

14:38.920 --> 14:42.090
THE SPECIAL DETECTIVE  SERIES.

14:42.130 --> 14:45.460
THE DETECTIVE WITH THE...
NOSE.

14:45.510 --> 14:47.510
GIVE YOURSELVES A
ROUND OF APPLAUSE.

14:47.550 --> 14:49.340
-&lt;CLINK&gt;
-WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING?

14:49.390 --> 14:53.680
OH! AS YOU KNOW, MY
MUSE IS HERE WITH ME TODAY.

14:53.720 --> 15:00.270
THE ORIGINAL SPECIAL
DETECTIVE, JARED BOYLE!

15:00.310 --> 15:03.070
THEY'RE CRAZY ABOUT YOU.

15:03.110 --> 15:04.940
WAIT... THAT MAN.

15:04.980 --> 15:07.570
WHAT'S HE DOING HERE?
IS THAT A BOMB?

15:07.610 --> 15:09.030
-WHAT?
-WHAT!

15:09.070 --> 15:11.070
SECURITY, THAT MAN HAS A BOMB!
GET HIM OUT OF HERE!

15:11.120 --> 15:11.990
&lt;COMMOTION&gt;

15:12.030 --> 15:13.120
I HAVEN'T GOT A BOMB!

15:13.160 --> 15:14.870
GET YOUR HANDS OFF ME.

15:14.910 --> 15:19.870
OBVIOUSLY A FAN. YOU
CAN ONLY IMAGINE THE SICKOS

15:19.920 --> 15:21.960
I HAVE GLOM ONTO ME AS A

15:22.000 --> 15:28.260
CELEBRITY, THAT I AM. UH, WHAT
WAS I SAYING?

15:28.300 --> 15:30.050
YOU'RE WONDERFUL.

15:30.090 --> 15:32.470
GOOD NIGHT.

15:34.810 --> 15:38.350
MY APOLOGIES.
HE'S JUST A HACK...
DRUNK WRITER.

15:38.390 --> 15:41.440
-WHO ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
-YOU.

15:41.480 --> 15:43.060
&lt;VOMITING&gt;

15:43.110 --> 15:45.150
YOU KNOW, STEELE, THIS IS
ALL GETTING A BIT
HARD TO TAKE,

15:45.190 --> 15:49.030
AND TO BE QUITE FRANK, I'M
LOSING MY PATIENCE. WHAT THE
HELL IS WRONG WITH YOU?

15:49.700 --> 15:51.160
BIRD FLU.

15:51.200 --> 15:54.870
I HAVE BEEN WAKING UP
WITH ACHES IN THE MORNING.

15:54.910 --> 16:00.580
OKAY STEELE. IF YOU WANT
MY HELP, YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
START BEING HONEST WITH ME.

16:00.620 --> 16:02.290
I AM BEING HONEST WITH YOU.

16:02.330 --> 16:06.090
REALLY? YOUR NOTEBOOK HAS
NO NOTES IN IT, WHICH MEANS
YOU'RE PROBABLY NOT REALLY

16:06.130 --> 16:08.090
WRITING A BOOK.

16:09.550 --> 16:11.340
-I'M SORRY JAKE.
-&lt;CAR ENGINE&gt;

16:12.340 --> 16:15.140
OH, DEAR GOD.

16:15.180 --> 16:16.390
-YOU GOTTA BE KIDDING ME.
-&lt;DOORS SLAMMING&gt;

16:16.430 --> 16:18.680
-STEELE.
-&lt;DOOR SLAMMING&gt;

16:18.720 --> 16:20.600
WHO THE HELL IS THIS NOW?

16:20.640 --> 16:23.230
YOU DON'T NEED TO WORRY ABOUT
WHO I AM, MY FRIEND.
MY CONCERN IS WHO ARE YOU?

16:23.270 --> 16:25.110
HOW THE HELL DID YOU FIND ME?

16:25.150 --> 16:29.360
EASY. I TOLD THE PEOPLE
AT THE AIRPORT I WAS LOOKING
FOR A SLIMY, MEATHEAD WRITER.

16:29.400 --> 16:30.530
THEY DREW ME A MAP.

16:30.570 --> 16:32.910
THAT IS ACTUALLY, UH,
PRETTY FUNNY.

16:32.950 --> 16:35.030
-&lt;WHACK&gt;
-OW!

16:35.070 --> 16:36.490
I WANT WHAT YOU OWE ME,
STEELE.

16:36.530 --> 16:40.660
WHAT HE OWES - OW!
WHAT HE OWES YOU?
WHAT DOES HE OWE YOU?

16:40.700 --> 16:42.040
YOU OWE SOMETHING TO EVERYONE.

16:42.080 --> 16:43.460
-&lt;WHACK&gt;
-OW!

16:43.500 --> 16:46.630
-&lt;WHACK&gt;
-OW! STOP HITTING ME!

16:46.670 --> 16:48.300
THIS AIN'T OVER, STEELE.
I'M GETTING TIRED OF

16:48.340 --> 16:51.840
CHASING YOU AROUND FOR WHAT
WE BOTH KNOW IS RIGHTFULLY
MINE. COME ON, SWEETS.

16:51.880 --> 16:54.050
-ENCHANTE.
-&lt;WHACK&gt;

16:58.350 --> 17:01.100
THIS IS NOT HOW
I PICTURED MY LIFE.

17:03.270 --> 17:05.900
ALL RIGHT. YOU'RE GOOD.
YOU'RE GOOD.

17:05.940 --> 17:08.860
OKAY, I'M NO EXPERT,
BUT I THINK HE'S
GONNA BE FINE.

17:08.900 --> 17:11.440
SHOULD PROBABLY TAKE HIM TO
A DOCTOR THOUGH,
TAKE HIM TO NIKKI.

17:11.490 --> 17:15.160
YEAH, NOT LIKELY. LISTEN
I APPRECIATE YOU DOING THIS.

17:15.200 --> 17:17.070
I MEAN, I HOPE I DIDN'T
RUIN YOUR NIGHT.

17:17.120 --> 17:18.620
EH, IT'S FINE.

17:18.660 --> 17:21.250
GOOD TO SEE YA.

17:21.290 --> 17:25.790
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU TOO.
BUT I DO HAVE ONE
QUESTION THOUGH.

17:25.830 --> 17:27.290
HERE WE GO.

17:27.330 --> 17:29.710
WHAT, KATH, NOW
DON'T BE LIKE THAT. ALL RIGHT?
I'M JUST SAYING,

17:29.750 --> 17:32.970
YOU KNOW, YOU SHOW UP HERE
WITHOUT EVEN A PHONE CALL, AND

17:33.010 --> 17:35.970
-THEN YOU INVITE SOME BUM TO
MOVE INTO THE HOUSE--
-YOU KNOW, JAKE, THIS

17:36.010 --> 17:37.510
IS SO NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS,

17:37.550 --> 17:41.270
OKAY? AND HE'S NOT A BUM.
SO YOU DON'T JUDGE ME,
AND I'LL LAY OFF JUDGING YOU.

17:41.310 --> 17:44.100
WELL, IF YOU'RE TRYING TO GIVE
THE OLD MAN A HEART ATTACK,
YOU'RE DOING A GOOD JOB.

17:44.140 --> 17:46.440
JAKE!

17:46.480 --> 17:48.690
REMEMBER, I KNOW EVERYONE
YOU'VE EVER DATED.

17:48.730 --> 17:50.110
YOU'RE NOT A PRINCE.

17:50.150 --> 17:51.570
SO JUST DROP IT.

17:51.610 --> 17:54.240
-FINE.
-OKAY. I'M OFF.

17:56.070 --> 17:57.700
IF YOU'RE AROUND LATER,
CALL ME.

17:57.740 --> 17:59.870
IT'S NICE TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

17:59.910 --> 18:01.580
YEAH. YOU TOO.

18:08.960 --> 18:11.170
WHO WAS THE GUY WHO TRIED
TO REARRANGE YOUR FACE?

18:11.210 --> 18:14.130
PROBABLY A NEW
BOYFRIEND OF ONE OF
MY EX-WIVES

18:14.170 --> 18:16.260
OR SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

18:17.760 --> 18:20.970
STEELE, WHY SHOULD I
BELIEVE A WORD THAT YOU'RE

18:21.010 --> 18:24.270
SAYING? ALL RIGHT? YOU'VE BEEN
LYING TO ME FROM THE START.

18:24.310 --> 18:26.810
&lt;CRYING&gt;

18:27.850 --> 18:30.310
I'M SORRY.

18:30.360 --> 18:31.770
I HAVE REAL TROUBLE,

18:31.820 --> 18:34.440
SERIOUS TROUBLE WITH SOME
SERIOUS PEOPLE.

18:34.480 --> 18:36.280
&lt;PHONE RINGING&gt;

18:36.320 --> 18:38.360
NIKKI AGAIN? YOU
KNOW, IF YOU WANT MY ADVICE--

18:38.410 --> 18:40.620
I DO NOT WANT YOUR ADVICE.
AT ALL.

18:40.660 --> 18:42.330
CLEARLY.

18:42.370 --> 18:44.830
-SO ARE YOU OKAY?
-I FEEL TERRIBLE, JAKE.

18:44.870 --> 18:47.460
I-- I DO. OBVIOUSLY.

18:47.500 --> 18:50.330
I CAN'T BELIEVE I DID THAT
TO DAVID.

18:54.090 --> 18:55.880
&lt;SLAP&gt;

18:58.300 --> 19:01.220
WAS THAT ABSOLUTELY NECESSARY?

19:01.260 --> 19:05.310
SO, HMM? YOU REALLY
THINK THAT WOULD WORK,

19:05.350 --> 19:06.890
GETTING ME THROWN OUT
LIKE THAT?

19:06.930 --> 19:10.850
GERHARDT, IT'S SO GOOD TO
SEE YOU, BUT I DID YOU A
FAVOR. IT WAS AN AWFUL PARTY.

19:10.900 --> 19:12.650
WHAT ARE YOU DOING IN
ST. JOHN'S?

19:12.690 --> 19:15.150
I CAME TO HELP YOU.

19:15.190 --> 19:17.240
-I KNOW PEOPLE--
-NO, NO, NO.

19:17.280 --> 19:20.990
I DON'T WANT HELP.
I WANT MY MONEY. YEAH?

19:22.120 --> 19:23.990
YOU HAVE UNTIL TOMORROW.

19:24.030 --> 19:25.540
I'M GOOD FOR IT.

19:25.580 --> 19:27.960
YOU'D BETTER BE.

19:28.000 --> 19:31.210
OH, AND STAY OUT OF
MY BUSINESS WITH TAMARA,
ALL RIGHT?

19:31.250 --> 19:33.540
-OH, ABSOLUTELY.
YES, OF COURSE.
-YOU KNOW...

19:34.170 --> 19:36.170
&lt;LAUGHS&gt;

19:36.210 --> 19:38.090
YOU MAY NOT BELIEVE THIS,
BUT, UM,

19:38.130 --> 19:39.840
I ALWAYS WANTED TO BE
A WRITER AS WELL.

19:39.880 --> 19:44.430
-REALLY, THAT'S FASCINATING.
-MMM. YOU KNOW, IF WE
ACTUALLY GET THROUGH THIS,

19:44.470 --> 19:46.600
YOU KNOW, IF I DON'T END UP
HAVING TO KILL YOU, I'D,

19:46.640 --> 19:48.020
UH... WELL,

19:48.060 --> 19:50.520
I'D REALLY APPRECIATE YOU
READING SOME OF MY STUFF.

19:50.560 --> 19:52.230
WELL, UH,
BOY, I'D LOVE TO, BUT

19:52.270 --> 19:53.860
MY LAWYERS DON'T USUALLY
LIKE ME READING--

19:53.900 --> 19:55.570
NO, NO, NO, NO. NO,
NO, YOU'LL READ IT.

19:55.610 --> 20:00.070
YOU'LL READ IT.
AND, AND, AND I DON'T WANT
ANY FALSE PRAISE, YOU KNOW?

20:00.110 --> 20:03.570
I WANT, I WANT WHAT YOU THINK,
TRUTHFULLY, YEAH?

20:03.620 --> 20:06.580
I THINK-- I THINK WE
CAN ABSOLUTELY ARRANGE
SOMETHING. ABSOLUTELY.

20:07.740 --> 20:09.370
ALL RIGHT.

20:09.410 --> 20:11.620
SO TOMORROW, STEELE.

20:13.000 --> 20:15.500
MY MONEY OR YOU'RE A DEAD MAN.

20:15.540 --> 20:17.750
&lt;BAR CHATTER&gt;

20:24.590 --> 20:25.930
&lt;LAUGHING&gt;

20:25.970 --> 20:28.720
LET'S HOOK UP LATER AND
WE'LL... I MEAN, WE'LL TALK.

20:28.770 --> 20:31.690
WE'RE NOT GONNA HOOK UP.
OKAY? I DON'T MEAN LET'S
HOOK UP LATER,

20:31.730 --> 20:33.600
I MEAN LET'S TALK. LATER.

20:33.650 --> 20:37.440
OKAY, OKAY.
BUT SHOULD I TELL DAVID?

20:37.480 --> 20:42.740
NO. I WOULD DEFINITELY
PUT A PIN IN THAT. FOR NOW.

20:42.780 --> 20:45.820
OKAY, FINE.
WELL, I-- I'M ON THE NIGHT
SHIFT SO I HAVE TO GO.

20:46.530 --> 20:48.290
OKAY. GOOD NIGHT.

21:01.840 --> 21:04.220
YOU SON OF A--!

21:07.470 --> 21:09.390
[MAL] SO, YOU LOST HIM.

21:09.430 --> 21:12.020
AND HE STOLE MY
FRIGGIN' WALLET.

21:12.060 --> 21:17.940
THOSE ARE STEELE'S FLIGHT
ITINERARIES. HE FLEW FIRST
CLASS FROM NEW YORK TO PARIS,

21:17.980 --> 21:20.650
EXECUTIVE FIRST CLASS FROM
PARIS TO COPENHAGEN--

21:20.690 --> 21:23.400
OKAY, ARE YOU JUST RUBBING IN
THE FACT THAT HE
STOLE MY CREDIT CARDS OR WHAT?

21:23.450 --> 21:24.650
NO, THAT'S THE WHOLE POINT.

21:24.700 --> 21:27.370
HE FLEW DISCOUNT ECONOMY
FROM DENMARK TO ST. JOHN'S.

21:27.410 --> 21:30.410
DISCOUNT?
DOESN'T SOUND LIKE GARRISON.

21:31.370 --> 21:33.870
HE'S BROKE.

21:33.910 --> 21:37.290
DIDN'T TAMARA SAY THAT
SHE WORKED AT THE
DANISH CONSULATE?

21:37.330 --> 21:39.340
OBVIOUSLY SOMETHING
WENT DOWN IN DENMARK.

21:39.380 --> 21:41.130
YEAH, BUT WHAT?

21:41.170 --> 21:43.590
LET'S FIND STEELE AND ASK HIM.

21:43.630 --> 21:47.470
SO THAT'S PRETTY COOL,
HAVING YOUR MOM HOME, HUH?
SHE SEEMS REALLY COOL.

21:47.510 --> 21:49.550
WHATEVER.

21:49.600 --> 21:51.890
WHY DON'T YOU GIVE ME SOME
GARRISON STEELE PITCHES?

21:51.930 --> 21:53.600
DO YOU REALLY WANT TO
HEAR THEM?

21:53.640 --> 21:57.520
ANYTHING TO GET YOU TO
STOP TALKING ABOUT MY MOM.
GO ON.

21:57.560 --> 22:00.360
OKAY. ALL RIGHT. OKAY.
YOU READY?

22:00.400 --> 22:03.860
-&lt;PHONE RINGING&gt;
-UH, OH! OH, THAT'S JAKE,

22:03.900 --> 22:06.410
I SHOULD PROBABLY...
YO, JAKE, WHAT'S UP? HEY

22:06.450 --> 22:08.070
IS, UH, GARRISON THERE,
BECAUSE

22:08.120 --> 22:10.450
I REALLY NEED TO TALK TO HIM
REGARDING A SENSITIVE
CREATIVE MATTER.

22:10.490 --> 22:13.580
DES, I NEED YOU TO TRACK
MY CREDIT CARDS, RIGHT AWAY.

22:13.620 --> 22:15.250
YEAH, YEAH, NO SWEAT, HOMMIE.
HANG ON, JUST LET ME SEE

22:15.290 --> 22:16.710
IF THERE'S ANY REAL-TIME
CHARGES.

22:16.750 --> 22:18.380
JUST DOING SOME
WORK FOR JAKE.

22:18.420 --> 22:21.420
UH... HANG ON.

22:23.050 --> 22:26.090
OH. HAVE YOU BEEN DRINKING AT
EIGHT DIFFERENT BARS

22:26.130 --> 22:28.550
ON GEORGE STREET
IN THE LAST HOUR?

22:28.590 --> 22:31.810
NO, BUT I THINK I KNOW
WHO HAS. UH...

22:31.850 --> 22:35.310
OH WAIT. HEY! WHILE I
STILL HAVE YOU, WHICH TITLE DO
YOU LIKE MORE:

22:35.350 --> 22:39.650
MURDER, MURDER ON THE WALL,
OR--
HELLO? HELLO? JAKE?

22:39.690 --> 22:44.400
LISTEN, I HAVE TO GO FIND
STEELE BEFORE HE FRIGGIN'
BANKRUPTS ME.

22:45.900 --> 22:49.160
BUT I GOTTA STOP
AT THE HOSPITAL FOR A...

22:49.200 --> 22:51.410
SOMETHING, REAL QUICK.

22:51.450 --> 22:57.580
-&lt;CLEARS THROAT&gt;
-NIKKI AGAIN, HUH?
OH, JAKE, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

22:57.620 --> 23:01.630
DON'T GET ME STARTED.
I THINK HE'S SEEING HER AGAIN.

23:01.670 --> 23:03.250
I OUGHTA WHACK THE
CRAP OUT OF HIM.

23:03.300 --> 23:06.050
OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT, YOU MIGHT
WANT TO TRY SOMETHING A
LITTLE DIFFERENT, YOU KNOW?

23:06.090 --> 23:08.340
A DIFFERENT TACTIC, MAYBE?
TALK IT THROUGH MAYBE?

23:08.380 --> 23:10.680
YEAH. MAYBE.

23:10.720 --> 23:12.180
-&lt;WHACK&gt;
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING
WITH NIKKI?

23:12.220 --> 23:14.470
ARE YOU PLANNING TO MAKE
HER ENTIRE LIFE A LIVING HELL?

23:14.510 --> 23:16.480
-&lt;WHACK&gt;
-OW! WHAT THE HELL ARE
YOU DOING?

23:16.520 --> 23:17.890
&lt;WHACK&gt;

23:17.930 --> 23:20.480
ROSE THOUGHT YOU MIGHT
WANT TO DISCUSS YOUR SITUATION

23:20.520 --> 23:22.440
WITH NIKKI,
SO HERE I AM TO DISCUSS IT.

23:22.480 --> 23:23.650
-&lt;WHACK&gt;
-OKAY, STOP HITTING ME.

23:23.690 --> 23:24.770
NO, I WON'T.

23:24.820 --> 23:26.280
OKAY, LOOK,
IT'S NOT MY FAULT YOU'RE

23:26.320 --> 23:29.240
IN A BAD MOOD BECAUSE YOU'RE
SUCH A TERRIBLE FATHER.

23:29.280 --> 23:30.700
LOOK, DON'T PUSH ME TODAY.

23:30.740 --> 23:35.160
I MEAN IT. THIS ISN'T ABOUT
ANY OF THAT.
THIS IS ABOUT YOU AND NIKKI.

23:35.200 --> 23:38.620
I PARKED THE CAR RIGHT HERE.

23:38.660 --> 23:43.500
UGH! WHY IS STEELE ALWAYS
TAKING MY FRIGGIN' CAR?

23:43.540 --> 23:45.460
BECAUSE HE KNOWS IT
BOTHERS YOU.

23:45.500 --> 23:51.590
ALL RIGHT LOOK, I NEED YOU
TO... TAKE ME TO THE HOSPITAL
TO GO SEE NIKKI.

23:53.090 --> 23:54.600
&lt;SIGH&gt;

23:55.600 --> 23:57.140
SATURDAY YOU WANNA HANG OUT?

23:57.180 --> 24:00.440
I'M BUSY.
WORK STUFF FOR UNCLE JAKE.

24:00.480 --> 24:03.730
DON'T BE A SNOT. I JUST
GOT HOME. IT'D BE NICE TO
HANG OUT, THAT'S ALL.

24:03.770 --> 24:05.570
HEY.

24:05.610 --> 24:08.650
LOOK AT THAT.
HE MANAGED TO FIND HIS PANTS.

24:09.400 --> 24:10.530
BANG UP JOB, COCKY.

24:10.570 --> 24:12.860
-TINNY.
-I'LL SEE YOU CATS LATER.

24:18.330 --> 24:19.580
WHAT?

24:21.410 --> 24:22.960
&lt;DOOR SHUTTING&gt;

24:24.920 --> 24:30.590
I SEEM TO HAVE THIS CONSTANT,
CHRONIC PAIN IN MY...
GUILT AREA.

24:30.630 --> 24:34.550
YEAH, I KNOW THE FEELING.
IT WAS A BAD IDEA,
WHAT WE DID.

24:35.510 --> 24:37.260
I COULDN'T AGREE MORE.

24:37.310 --> 24:39.640
YOU DON'T NEED TO BE SO
ENTHUSIASTIC ABOUT IT.

24:39.680 --> 24:41.180
NO, NO, NIKKI, COME ON.

24:41.230 --> 24:42.560
&lt;FRUSTRATED GROAN&gt;

24:42.600 --> 24:44.900
COME ON. SERIOUSLY.
THINK ABOUT IT.
WE'VE BEEN THROUGH THIS.

24:44.940 --> 24:47.190
WE'VE DONE IT OVER AND
OVER AND OVER AGAIN.
IT WAS A--

24:47.230 --> 24:49.690
HORRIBLE IDEA.
