37:15.810 --> 37:16.860
WHAT DID HE WANT?

37:16.900 --> 37:19.280
I DON'T KNOW. HIS "ITEM".

37:19.320 --> 37:21.570
BUT WE GAVE HIM THE
CAVIAR IN A LOVELY BAG.

37:21.610 --> 37:23.360
WHAT MORE COULD HE WANT?

37:23.400 --> 37:25.450
-ROSE?
-HMM?

37:25.490 --> 37:28.410
DID YOU DO THAT SEARCH OF
RECENT THEFT AND
CRIME ACTIVITY

37:28.450 --> 37:29.870
IN DENMARK?

37:29.910 --> 37:31.250
YES, I DID, AND THAT

37:31.290 --> 37:32.540
DIDN'T REALLY TURN UP MUCH.

37:32.580 --> 37:34.500
THERE WAS A BANK ROBBERY,
MUSEUM

37:34.540 --> 37:37.040
THEFT AND A BIG
ELECTRONIC EXPO WAS HIT,

37:37.080 --> 37:38.840
BUT THAT'S ABOUT IT FOR
THE LAST COUPLE OF MONTHS.

37:38.880 --> 37:41.880
MUSEUM THEFT.

37:41.920 --> 37:43.800
-ARE YOU THINKING
WHAT I'M THINKING?
-YEAH.

37:43.840 --> 37:45.630
WE'RE GOING TO NEED
DES' SPECIAL SKILLS.

37:45.680 --> 37:50.470
-WHICH ONES, B'Y?
-&lt;CRASH&gt;

37:50.510 --> 37:52.600
[TAMARA] GARRISON STEELE IS
NOT GOING TO SHOW UP.

37:52.640 --> 37:54.390
WHY WOULD HE SHOW UP?

37:54.440 --> 37:57.610
I'LL TELL YOU WHY.
BECAUSE YOU ARE ABSOLUTELY
FETCHING AND I FEEL SLIGHTLY

37:57.650 --> 38:00.320
RESPONSIBLE FOR PUTTING YOU IN
THAT POSITION.

38:00.360 --> 38:01.440
SLIGHTLY RESPONSIBLE?

38:01.480 --> 38:03.190
YOU'RE DIRECTLY RESPONSIBLE!

38:03.240 --> 38:06.410
-NOBODY ASKED YOU.
-GARRISON. FIRST OF ALL,

38:06.450 --> 38:08.240
I'VE GOT MY SHORT STORY FOR
YOU TO READ.

38:08.280 --> 38:12.450
NOW IT'S A FIRST DRAFT,
BUT I WANT YOU TO BE HONEST.
KIND, BUT HONEST.

38:12.500 --> 38:13.910
GOOD GOD. SHORT?

38:13.950 --> 38:16.120
AND SECONDLY,
DID YOU BRING MY ITEM?

38:16.170 --> 38:19.590
I'M GONNA BE HONEST. AT FIRST,
I HAD NO IDEA WHAT IN THE
HELL YOU WERE TALKING ABOUT.

38:19.630 --> 38:23.090
I MEAN, ITEM?
AND THEN IT DAWNED ON ME.

38:23.130 --> 38:26.800
REALLY QUITE BRILLIANT
FOR YOU DO BE USING THE CAVIAR

38:26.840 --> 38:32.100
TO HIDE WHAT YOU ARE ACTUALLY
SMUGGLING.

38:32.140 --> 38:34.310
COME ON, ENOUGH CHIT-CHAT.
JUST GIVE ME THE SKETCH.

38:34.350 --> 38:35.390
A MAGNUSSEN SKETCH.

38:35.430 --> 38:37.850
THAT WAS STOLEN THREE
MONTHS AGO. IT'S PRICELESS.

38:38.730 --> 38:39.940
&lt;CLICK&gt;

38:39.980 --> 38:41.320
HEY, HEY, HEY!
DON'T DO ANYTHING RASH THERE.

38:41.360 --> 38:44.150
OKAY NOW, YOU CAN SHOOT ME,
I DROP THIS, THE PAINTING

38:44.190 --> 38:49.450
GOES UP IN FLAMES, OR YOU GIVE
STEELE THE KEYS TO THE
HANDCUFFS AND YOU LET HER GO.

38:52.410 --> 38:54.040
FINE.

38:57.580 --> 39:00.580
PLEASE KNOW THIS WAS ALWAYS
MY PLAN. HOW COULD I ABANDON

39:00.630 --> 39:03.590
A CREATURE AS
BEAUTIFUL AS YOU?

39:03.630 --> 39:05.590
COME ON. YOU GOT THE GIRL.
GIVE ME THE SKETCH.

39:05.630 --> 39:07.380
YEAH...

39:07.420 --> 39:09.510
OH! YOU IDIOT!

39:09.550 --> 39:10.590
GERHARDT?

39:10.640 --> 39:11.720
&lt;WHACK&gt;

39:11.760 --> 39:13.760
-THAT'S FOR EARLIER.
-&lt;CLANG&gt;

39:15.430 --> 39:16.560
NICE WORK.

39:16.600 --> 39:19.520
NOW THAT'S MORE LIKE IT.
TOO BAD YOU HAD TO BURN A

39:19.560 --> 39:22.360
BEAUTIFUL PIECE OF ART TO
SAVE A MASTERPIECE.

39:26.110 --> 39:31.410
I GOTTA BE HONEST WITH YOU.
I'M A BIGGER FAN OF AN
ORIGINAL MYSELF.

39:31.450 --> 39:33.240
WHAT A REVEAL.

39:33.280 --> 39:36.160
IT'S PERFECT.

39:36.200 --> 39:41.330
SO I TOOK A PHOTO OF THE
SKETCH, THEN I MADE A STENCIL,
AND THEN I USED SPRAY PAINT TO

39:41.380 --> 39:42.840
MAKE THE FORGERY.

39:42.880 --> 39:44.130
-I DON'T CARE.
-REALLY?

39:44.170 --> 39:46.340
WELL, IT KIND OF MAKES ME THE
BANKSY OF NEWFOUNDLAND.

39:46.380 --> 39:48.340
MORE LIKE THE BELL-HEAD
OF OUTER COVE.

39:48.380 --> 39:49.470
NICE.

39:49.510 --> 39:51.640
-BUT IT IS A GOOD JOB THOUGH.
-THANKS.

39:51.680 --> 39:52.850
-SO, GO AWAY NOW.
-WHY?

39:52.890 --> 39:54.640
-GO.
-OH.

39:57.560 --> 39:59.600
THE LOVE CANAL?

39:59.640 --> 40:01.150
I'M SENSING A HIT.

40:01.190 --> 40:05.150
YEAH, IT'S WRITTEN BY
FORD PLATINUM, THAT'S GARRISON
STEELE'S PSEUDONYM WHEN HE

40:05.190 --> 40:09.700
WRITES... ADULT NOVELS. I CAN
GET YOU AN AUTOGRAPHED COPY
IF YOU WANT.

40:09.740 --> 40:12.820
I'LL PASS. THANKS.

40:12.870 --> 40:14.700
YOU WOULDN'T HAPPEN TO KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT

40:14.740 --> 40:16.950
AN INTERNATIONAL SMUGGLER,

40:16.990 --> 40:18.540
OR A PRICELESS SKETCH
SHOWING UP AT

40:18.580 --> 40:19.660
THE STATION TODAY?

40:19.710 --> 40:22.880
NO. I MEAN, THAT SOUNDS
LIKE A CHEESY PLOT FROM
THIS NOVEL.

40:22.920 --> 40:24.790
WELL, IT'S-- IT'S REAL.

40:24.840 --> 40:26.460
AND FOR THE RECORD,
IT WAS HUGE.

40:26.500 --> 40:30.380
LIKE AN INTERNATIONAL SEARCH
KIND OF THING. SO...

40:30.420 --> 40:33.010
IS THAT YOUR WAY OF
TRYING TO PAY ME A COMPLIMENT?

40:33.050 --> 40:36.060
GOD, NO.

40:36.100 --> 40:42.100
LISTEN, ABOUT THE GUY YOU
WERE WITH AT THE DANISH
CONSULATE PARTY. YOUR DATE.

40:42.140 --> 40:48.320
THINGS GOING WELL?
IS THERE SOMETHING REAL THERE
BETWEEN YOU TWO?

40:50.530 --> 40:54.490
MAYBE. I DON'T KNOW.

40:55.910 --> 40:58.990
&lt;PHONE RINGING&gt;

40:59.660 --> 41:01.870
I'M SORRY.

41:02.540 --> 41:05.330
I'LL SEE YOU AROUND, DOYLE.

41:08.550 --> 41:12.300
-NIKKI, I--
-YOU KNOW, THE LAST TIME
WE SAID WE LOVED EACH OTHER,

41:12.340 --> 41:13.880
WE ENDED UP MARRIED.

41:13.930 --> 41:16.350
YEAH, AND WE BOTH KNOW
HOW THAT TURNED OUT.

41:16.390 --> 41:19.560
IT'S LIKE WE GO TO THIS
PLACE WHERE IT'S THE SEX
AND NOT THE LOVE TALKING.

41:19.600 --> 41:24.270
LIKE, I KNOW I LOVE YOU BUT,
I DON'T "LOVE" LOVE YOU,
OBVIOUSLY.

41:24.310 --> 41:26.650
I COULDN'T AGREE MORE, SO
MAYBE WE SHOULD BOTH JUST PUT

41:26.690 --> 41:29.480
THIS WHOLE THING BEHIND US,
YEAH?

41:29.530 --> 41:30.570
BUT, UH, ABOUT DAVID.

41:30.610 --> 41:33.450
NIKKI, I KNOW YOU FEEL
GUILTY, BUT THERE'S NO POINT

41:33.490 --> 41:35.610
IN TELLING DAVID ANYTHING.

41:36.950 --> 41:38.370
NEVER MIND.

41:38.410 --> 41:39.740
NOTHING.

41:39.790 --> 41:42.040
TALK TO YA, 'KAY?

41:59.640 --> 42:00.720
WELL, LOOK AT YOU.

42:00.760 --> 42:03.100
YOU LOOK... GREAT.

42:03.140 --> 42:06.520
WELL, A MAN MUST LOOK THE PART
WHEN HE'S A "HEAVY WEIGHT".

42:06.560 --> 42:08.060
GARRISON, COME ON.
WE'RE GOING TO MISS
OUR FLIGHT.

42:10.020 --> 42:11.730
TURNS OUT SHE IS THE

42:11.780 --> 42:13.820
LOVE OF MY LIFE.

42:13.860 --> 42:15.240
WE'RE HEADING TO DENMARK
TO TESTIFY AGAINST

42:15.280 --> 42:16.570
GERHARDT, AND THE COURT HAS

42:16.610 --> 42:19.530
DROPPED THE CHARGES AGAINST
TAMARA IN EXCHANGE FOR

42:19.580 --> 42:21.660
RECOVERING THE SKETCH.

42:21.700 --> 42:23.830
AND THEN WE'RE OFF TO VEGAS.

42:26.580 --> 42:28.210
I'LL BE IN THE LOO.

42:28.250 --> 42:29.790
SEE YOU SHORTLY, MY DARLING.

42:29.840 --> 42:32.130
LIKE THEY SAY, THE FIFTH
TIME'S THE CHARM, WHAT?

42:32.170 --> 42:37.300
AND LISTEN, I'M NOT FORGETTING
YOU OWE ME A PIECE OF
THIS BOOK AND NOT THE

42:37.340 --> 42:39.390
-GARBAGE YOU'RE WRITING
FOR JAVIER.
-"JAVIAR".

42:39.430 --> 42:41.510
-WHATEVER.
-NO WORRIES.

42:41.560 --> 42:44.810
TAMARA'S MY NEW ASSISTANT,
AND THANKS TO THIS LATEST
ADVENTURE I HAVE THE

42:44.850 --> 42:46.060
IDEA FOR MY NEXT NOVEL.

42:46.100 --> 42:48.730
LET ME GUESS, ANOTHER SPECIAL DETECTIVE  ?

42:48.770 --> 42:51.770
NO, I HAVE DISCOVERED A
MUCH GREATER PROTAGONIST.

42:51.820 --> 42:54.190
WHO? DES?

42:54.230 --> 42:55.530
ME.

42:55.570 --> 42:57.820
THIS WILL BE THE FIRST BOOK
IN MY NEW SERIES

42:57.860 --> 43:01.200
